READ THE DATA
In [ ]:
path = '../input/plantvillage-dataset/color'

# Specify class names
class_names = sorted(os.listdir(path))

# Create training and testing datasets
train_ds = tf.keras.utils.image_dataset_from_directory(
    path,
    image_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=64,
    seed=500,
    validation_split=0.2,
    subset='training',
    shuffle=True,  # Shuffle the training data
    class_names=class_names
)

test_ds = tf.keras.utils.image_dataset_from_directory(
    path,
    image_size=(224, 224),
    batch_size=64,
    seed=500,
    validation_split=0.2,
    subset='validation',
    shuffle=False,  # No need to shuffle the testing data
    class_names=class_names
)

# Prefetch the datasets
train_ds = train_ds.prefetch(tf.data.AUTOTUNE)
test_ds = test_ds.prefetch(tf.data.AUTOTUNE)

def show_image(image_path, title):
    image = cv2.imread(image_path)

    plt.figure(figsize = (6,6))
    plt.imshow(image)
    plt.title(title,size =18 )
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.show()

Build Neural network [CNN]
In [ ]:
model = keras.Sequential([
    keras.layers.Rescaling(scale = 1/255 , input_shape =(224,224,3) ) ,

    keras.layers.Conv2D(32 , (3,3) , activation = 'relu'),
    keras.layers.MaxPool2D((2,2))                     ,
    keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),

    keras.layers.Conv2D(64 , (3,3) , activation = 'relu') ,
    keras.layers.MaxPool2D((2,2)) ,
    keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),

    keras.layers.Conv2D(64 , (3,3) , activation = 'relu') ,
    keras.layers.MaxPool2D((2,2)) ,
    keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),

    keras.layers.Conv2D(64 , (3,3) , activation = 'relu') ,
    keras.layers.MaxPool2D((2,2)) ,
    keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),

    keras.layers.Conv2D(128 , (3,3) , activation = 'relu') ,
    keras.layers.MaxPool2D((2,2)) ,

    # fully connected layers
    keras.layers.Flatten(),
    keras.layers.Dense(512,activation = 'relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(128,activation = 'relu'),
    keras.layers.Dropout(0.2),
    keras.layers.Dense(64,activation = 'relu'),
    keras.layers.Dense(38,activation ='softmax')

])

VISUALISATION OF PREDICTIONS
In [ ]:
def img_to_pred(image):
  image = image.numpy()
  image = tf.expand_dims(image,0)
  return image
In [ ]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
plt.figure(figsize=(18,18))
for images, labels in test_ds.take(10) : 
  for i in range(1,4):
    plt.subplot(3,3,i)
    plt.imshow(images[i].numpy().astype('uint32'))
    plt.axis('off')
    actual = class_names[labels[i]]
    predict =class_names[np.argmax( model.predict(img_to_pred(images[i])))]
    plt.title(f"actual : {actual}  \n predicted : {predict} ")
